The paper presents a study of tree search techniques applied to a combinatorial optimization problem, the Sequential Ordering Problem. This problem is related to scheduling and routing, which are topics commonly studied in the Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming, which is a technique commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as iterative beam search (cs.LG) and search over inference. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm, which involves software engineering practices such as modularization and testing (cs.SE).
